
[1]armature

   'ARMATURE, n. [L. armatura.]

   1. Armor; that which defends the body. It comprehends whatever is worn
   for defense of the body, and has been sometimes used for offensive
   weapons. Armature, like arms and armor, is used also of the furniture
   of animals and vegetables, evidently intended for their protection; as
   prickles, spines and horns.

   2. In ancient military art, an exercise performed with missive weapons,
   as darts, spears and arrows.
